47.73	Secret_ballot	Secret ballot	The secret ballot is a voting method in which a voter's choices in an election or a referendum are anonymous. The key aim is to ensure the voter records a sincere choice by forestalling attempts to influence the voter by intimidation or bribery. The system is one means of achieving the goal of political privacy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/65/William_Hogarth_031.jpg/320px-William_Hogarth_031.jpg
